# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  VerseBase Discord builder — environment
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Copy this file to ".env" (same folder) and fill in the token.
#  The real .env is git-ignored and must never be committed.
#
#  How to get the token (~2 min):
#    1. https://discord.com/developers/applications  →  New Application
#    2. Name it "VerseBase", open the "Bot" tab
#    3. "Reset Token" → Copy → paste it below
#    4. Invite the bot to your empty server with Administrator
#       (the README has a ready-made invite URL)
#    5. From this /discord folder:  npm install  &&  npm run build
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

DISCORD_TOKEN=paste-your-bot-token-here

# Optional. Only needed if the bot is in more than one server.
# Enable Developer Mode in Discord (Settings → Advanced), then
# right-click the server icon → "Copy Server ID".
# GUILD_ID=
